title: Staircase, Cloister of St. Maclou, Rouen
medium: Graphite on gray paperboard tipped into binding with fabric
description: Vertical sheet depicting a late medieval or early Renaissance era half-timbered and plastered building.  At left a simple, covered staircase rises to the second floor.  The staircase casts a deep shadow along an adjacent opening at the first floor.  To the right and above this are rows of windows set into flattened arches, each with a prominent keystone.
name: Album page
